  <!-- Body -->
  <div style="padding:3rem 0 7rem;">
    <div class="max-w-[780px] mx-auto px-8" style="font-size:0.97rem;color:var(--color-text-secondary);line-height:1.9;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:1.75rem;">

      <p>Teneriffe occupies a bend in the Brisbane River between New Farm and Newstead, and it is defined in most buyers' minds by two things: the converted woolstore apartments along the riverfront and the elevated freestanding homes on the streets above them. Both segments operate at the prestige end of Brisbane's inner-city residential market, but they attract different buyers and require different approaches. The suburb is tightly held, with low annual transaction volumes, which means that each sale carries weight in setting the market for the next one.</p>

      <p>The woolstore conversions are among Brisbane's most recognisable residential buildings: high ceilings, exposed brick, polished concrete and riverfront position create a product that has no direct equivalent elsewhere in the city. This uniqueness is an asset when positioning for sale, but it also means there are fewer direct comparables, which requires careful and considered pricing rather than a simple median benchmark.</p>

      <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif);font-size:1.5rem;font-weight:400;color:var(--color-text-primary);">Who is buying in Teneriffe</h2>
      <p>Affluent professionals and couples seeking a premium inner-city lifestyle are the core of the Teneriffe buyer pool. Many are downsizing from larger homes in New Farm or Ascot but unwilling to sacrifice inner-city access or the quality of their living environment. Interstate buyers, particularly from Sydney and Melbourne, are an important segment in Teneriffe because the suburb's profile extends nationally and the comparative value of Brisbane's premier riverside address relative to equivalent Sydney locations remains compelling. The woolstore apartments appeal to buyers who are specifically seeking the industrial-heritage aesthetic and would not substitute a conventional apartment in a nearby building.</p>

      <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif);font-size:1.5rem;font-weight:400;color:var(--color-text-primary);">What drives value in Teneriffe</h2>
      <p>River frontage and direct river views are the primary premium drivers. For the woolstore apartments, the floor level, aspect and the size of the apartment within the building are the key differentiators, with riverfront-facing apartments and those on higher floors consistently achieving the strongest results. For the freestanding homes on the residential streets above the river, the quality and modernity of the renovation, the outdoor entertaining quality and the city or river view, where present, are the variables that drive premiums. Body corporate fees and sinking fund health are scrutinised carefully by buyers at this level, particularly for the woolstore buildings where major maintenance decisions can have significant cost implications.</p>

      <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif);font-size:1.5rem;font-weight:400;color:var(--color-text-primary);">Preparing for sale</h2>
      <p>At the Teneriffe price point, presentation is expected to be excellent. Buyers comparing properties in this suburb and in New Farm and Newstead are making assessments based on quality of finish and lifestyle feel, and anything that looks tired or neglected will be reflected in offers. For woolstore apartments, the emphasis should be on showcasing the architectural elements: ensure the exposed brick is clean, the polished concrete floors are in good condition, and the lighting highlights the volume and character of the space. Professional styling that complements the industrial aesthetic rather than fighting it will consistently outperform generic contemporary staging.</p>

      <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif);font-size:1.5rem;font-weight:400;color:var(--color-text-primary);">Campaign approach</h2>
      <p>The limited supply and strong demand for quality properties in Teneriffe can support auction for well-positioned properties where competing buyer interest is genuine. For the woolstore apartments, where the buyer pool is specific and often includes interstate buyers who require time to arrange travel and due diligence, expressions of interest or private treaty with a structured timeline can generate better outcomes than a public auction that disadvantages remote buyers. The marketing must reach interstate and national audiences, because local search alone will not capture all of the genuine buyers for a premier Teneriffe property. Agent networks, national portals and targeted digital marketing to the right demographic are all components of an effective campaign at this level.</p>


      <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif);font-size:1.5rem;font-weight:400;color:var(--color-text-primary);">Best time to sell in Teneriffe</h2>
      <p>Teneriffe is the prestige woolstore and riverfront precinct that adjoins New Farm, and its selling market operates on a prestige timeline. Autumn (February to April) is the primary selling window: buyers who have been assessing the Teneriffe-New Farm precinct through summer arrive in February with a clear brief and the financial readiness to act. The woolstore apartment segment, Teneriffe's most iconic housing typology, attracts a buyer who is making a considered lifestyle decision, and those buyers respond to a well-structured autumn campaign. Spring also performs, particularly for terrace homes and townhouses that benefit from the suburb's gardens and the riverside walking trail being at their peak. Interstate buyers, particularly from Sydney and Melbourne who are relocating to Brisbane, are consistently present in Teneriffe year-round and respond to the precinct's unique character regardless of season.</p>

      <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif);font-size:1.5rem;font-weight:400;color:var(--color-text-primary);">How long does it take to sell in Teneriffe</h2>
      <p>Teneriffe properties typically spend 32 to 48 days on market. The market is stratified by typology: woolstore apartments in the best buildings (Stratton, Newstead Central, The Hill) move significantly faster than generic apartment stock in the suburb's newer residential towers. Buyers for the iconic woolstore buildings have detailed knowledge of the individual buildings, their body corporate history, sinking fund health, and owner-occupier profiles, a well-presented woolstore apartment in a well-managed building moves in 25 to 35 days. Townhouses and terrace homes attract a smaller buyer pool but a deeply committed one. Teneriffe's dining and lifestyle strip on Vernon Terrace is a genuine buyer motivator and should feature prominently in any campaign.</p>

